name: ZIPPlus4Code
definition: nine-digit number consisting of five digits, a hyphen, and four digits, which the USPS describes by its trademark ZIP+4
label: ZIP+4 Code
explanatoryNote: The correct format for a numeric ZIP+4 code is five digits, a hyphen, and four digits. The first five digits represent the 5-digit ZIP Code; the sixth and seventh digits (the first two after the hyphen) identify an area known as a sector; the eighth and ninth digits identify a smaller area known as a segment. Together, the final four digits identify geographic units such as a side of a street between intersections, both sides of a street between intersections, a building, a floor or group of floors in a building, a firm within a building, a span of boxes on a rural route, or a group of Post Office boxes to which a single USPS employee makes delivery.

name: OverseasMilitaryAddress
label: overseas military address
definition: delivery address whose delivery address line uses an abbreviation for the unit or command such as 'CMR', 'PSC', or 'UNIT', or 'HC', followed by the unit identifier, followed by 'BOX' followed by box number, in place of a street address, either 'APO' or 'FPO' as the literal value for the city and the appropriate armed forces subdivision code in place of a subdivision (state) code

name: USPostalServiceAddressIdentifier
explanatoryNote: The delivery point digits are almost never printed on mail in human-readable form; instead they are encoded in the POSTNET delivery point barcode (DPBC) or as part of the newer Intelligent Mail Barcode (IMB).
label: U.S. Postal Service address identifier
definition: combined with the ZIP + 4 code, the delivery point code provides a unique identifier for every deliverable address served by the USPS

name: HighwayContractRouteAddress
label: highway contract address
definition: delivery address whose delivery address line uses the abbreviation 'HC', followed by the route identifier, followed by 'BOX' followed by box number, in place of a street address

name: DeliveryAddressCodeSet
definition: system of numeric codes that substitute for specified delivery point details according to the U.S. Postal Service Publication 28
label: delivery address code set

name: DeliveryPointCode
explanatoryNote: When combined with the ZIP + 4 code, the delivery point code provides a unique identifier for every deliverable address served by the USPS. The delivery point digits are almost never printed on mail in human-readable form; instead they are encoded in the POSTNET delivery point barcode (DPBC) or as part of the newer Intelligent Mail Barcode (IMB).
label: delivery point code
definition: specific set of digits between 00 and 99 assigned to a delivery point

name: DeliveryPointCodeSet
label: delivery point code set
definition: system of numeric codes that substitute for specified delivery point details according to the U.S. Postal Service Publication 28

name: ZipCodeScheme
definition: system used in the U.S. to facilitate the delivery of mail, consisting of a five- or nine-digit code Zone Improvement Plan (ZIP) printed directly after the address, the first five digits (initial code) indicating the state and post office or postal zone, the last four (expanded code) the box section or number, portion of a rural route, building, or other specific delivery location
label: zip code scheme

name: DepartmentOfStateAddress
definition: delivery address whose delivery address line uses 'UNIT' followed by the unit identifier, followed by 'BOX' followed by box number, in place of a street address, 'DPO' as the literal value for the city, and the appropriate armed forces subdivision code in place of a subdivision (state) code
label: Department of State address

name: ZIPCode
label: Zip Code
definition: five-digit code code assigned to a delivery address indicating the state and post office or postal zone

name: RuralRoute
definition: mail route outside the city or township limits in a rural area associated with an address
label: highway contract route address

name: PuertoRicoAddress
label: Puerto Rico address
definition: delivery address for a delivery point in Puerto Rico that may include a supplementary address line containing the abbreviation 'URB' followed by the name of the urbanization area that is appropriate for that address

name: GeneralDeliveryAddress
explanatoryNote: The value of the +4 component of a ZIP+4 code should be '9999'.
definition: delivery address that uses the words 'GENERAL DELIVERY', uppercase preferred, spelled out (no abbreviation), in place of a street address
label: general delivery address

name: StandardizedAddress
definition: delivery address that is fully spelled out, abbreviated by using the Postal Service standard abbreviations or as given in the current Postal Service ZIP+4 file
label: standardized address

name: PrivateMailBoxAddress
label: private mail box address
definition: delivery address provided by a commercial mail receiving company that includes a supplementary address line containing the abbreviation 'PMB' or the pound "#" symbol followed by the mailbox number; alternatively, 'PMB' or '#" and the mailbox number can be appended to the street address

name: DepartmentOfStateUnitComponent
label: Department of State unit component
definition: component of a Department of State address that includes 'UNIT' followed by the unit identifier

name: CompleteAddress
definition: delivery address that has all the address elements necessary to allow an exact match with the current Postal Service ZIP+4 and City State files to obtain the finest level of ZIP+4 and delivery point codes for the delivery address
explanatoryNote: A complete address may be required on mail at some automation rates.
label: complete address

name: RuralRouteAddress
definition: delivery address whose delivery address line uses the abbreviation 'RR', followed by the route identifier, followed by 'BOX' followed by box number, in place of a street address
label: rural route address

name: HighwayContractRoute
label: highway contract route
definition: highway contract route associated with an address

name: Mailbox
definition: mailbox, other than a U.S. Post Office box, associated with an address
label: mailbox

name: InternationalAddress
label: international address
definition: physical address that explicitly includes a country

name: Urbanization
label: urbanization
explanatoryNote: This URB descriptor, commonly used in urban areas of Puerto Rico, is an important part of the addressing format, as it describes the location of a given street.
definition: an area, sector, or development within a larger geographic area

name: hasUrbanization
definition: indicates area, sector, or development within a geographic area relevant to a delivery address
label: has urbanization

name: Northwest
label: Noroeste
definition: geographic directional symbol for Northwest

name: RuralRouteDesignator
definition: designator for a mail route outside the city or township limits in a rural area
label: rural route designator

name: South
definition: geographic directional symbol for South
label: South

name: East
label: Este
definition: geographic directional symbol for East

name: North
label: Norte
definition: geographic directional symbol for North

name: USPostOfficeBoxDesignator
label: post office box designator
definition: designator for a U.S. Post Office box

name: Southwest
definition: geographic directional symbol for Southwest
label: Suroeste

name: MailboxDesignator
label: mailbox designator
definition: designator for a mail box other than a U.S. Post Office box

name: Southeast
label: Sureste
definition: geographic directional symbol for Southeast

name: West
label: Oeste
definition: geographic directional symbol for West

name: Northeast
label: Northeast
definition: geographic directional symbol for Northeast

name: HighwayContractRouteDesignator
definition: designator for a route served by an independent contractor rather than directly by the U.S. Postal Service
label: highway contract route designator
